Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. result.caption: State of Wisconsin vs. Aaliyah Rae Frank

records.addlTxt: 4:06 PM Prosecuting attorney Alexander Paul Seifert in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Aaliyah Rae Frank in court.  Attorney Jeffery Joy appeared by video for Aaliyah Rae Frank. State here for PH and will be proceeding, calls first witness, Sgt. Luther Kelly. Sworn in, 4:07 PM. State directs. Record reflects proper identification of  the defendant, 4:18 PM. Joy cross-examines witness, 4:18 PM. State re-directs, 4:23 PM. Joy re-cross, 4:24 PM. Witness excused, 4:26 PM. Court based on evidence provided, finds probable cause, binds over for trial. Information has been filed. Joy has received information, will proceed to ARGN, waives reading of information and enters NG pleas. Court accepts pleas, continues bond and will have set for JT. If resolved with DA, contact JA for a PLEAS date.

1:32 PM Prosecuting attorney Charles James Simono in court for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant Aaliyah Rae Frank in court.  Plaintiff State of Wisconsin in court.  Attorney Jeffery Joy appeared by video for Aaliyah Rae Frank. State - here for a PH. Attorney Joy - asks Court for an adjournment of PH for stated reasons (family emergency), still investigating the case - working on defenses, apologizes to the Court, don't believe State would object. Court responds, no defenses at this state of the case. State responds, can start the PH today and would need to continue it at a later date as Sgt. Kelley is not in Court today - was subpoenaed on 6/24/22. Court reviews file, State does have one witness available in the Courtroom. Court will allow an adjournment of the PH, continues bond, sets for PH on 7/6/22 at 4:00 PM.
Preliminary hearing scheduled for July 6, 2022 at 04:00 pm.
Preliminary hearing on July 6, 2022 at 04:00 pm.
